steps.description:
Use the `{file.*}` placeholder syntax added in PR #5463 to load secrets from files. This replaces workarounds using environment variables or .env files.

Example Caddyfile using file-based placeholders:
```
example.com {
  tls {
    dns cloudflare {file./run/secrets/cf_api_token}
  }
}
```

For Docker secrets or systemd credentials, place the secret in a file and reference it with `{file./path/to/secret}`. The file contents are read at runtime and substituted into the configuration.
